Comment.val:
Print control from child programs requires some special handling. because Ctrl+P and User Action 13 (UA13) are linked in the menu
Ctrl+P => print complete report called from this program Left menu icon (UA13) => print active tab, needs to be called from detail program w. up-to-date settings
Implementation in child program
Tab parents (task with filter options and buttons) UA13 handler which calls the print program for the tab Ctrl+P handler which raises UserAction 1 to prevent CTRL+P default handling (which results in UA13)

Text.val: Ctrl+P print entire report
Ctrl+P is set as trigger for UA13 in the menu
The UA13 handler has to be declared above the Ctrl+P handler
So the CTRL+P handler will be executed instead of the UA13 when CtRL+P is used
-- See handler UserAction1 for remarks, why this trigger is necessary
-- UserAction1 has to be skipped, if GM313 - Switch client programs was called
and if still in process, beause some of the client programs which called via
GM313 triggers UserAction1 for their own usage, e.g. in OCA001 to check if
something is changed on the client attributes screen. In this case without the
test, if GM313 is still in process, the current UserAction1 is triggered from
e.g. OCA001 which resulted in the printing (like Ctrl+P) of the client
statistics
